Too Great and Terrible x 2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Bid 2, this way you will outbid most other Nazgul players and others who just bid low for safety reasons.  If you win the bid definately go first.  I play Farmer Maggot&#39;s pad because it helps very few decks out there, where as starting the Pony would definately help me, but help everyone else too.  It&#39;s also nice to go get Pippin to make Gandalf and Aragorn cheap against Nazgul and Helpful to get Merry who is a mini &quot;Trust Me as You Once Did&quot;.  If you start first, just move to 2 against Nazgul and Uruk-hai... this way you dictate the pace of the game.  For them to double move against you they will have to hit your ugly sites.  If they don&#39;t they give you another turn to get your fellowship set up before it can start moving at will.<br />
<br />
The size of the deck allows it to set up early and start hitting the shadow hard.  It&#39;s easy to double move when you can&#39;t spot any minions, so try to wipe out any opposition every turn.<br />
<br />
The Shadow side is built with the idea that your fellowship needs a couple of turns to set up, and then it is almost unstoppable.  Nazgul slow em down early like nobody&#39;s business, and possibly win a couple games for you early.<br />
<br />
Card Choices:<br />
Merry: Mini Trust Me... lunch on request<br />
Pippin: Cheaper Aragorn/Gandalf is always nice... also served upon request<br />
Arwen: Great against Nazgul, good everywhere else<br />
Boromir, Lord: Unkillable with Armor<br />
Betrayal of Isengard: Because Saruman can hurt big fellowships a bit too much...<br />
Ferny: Is there a more annoying minion in the game?<br />
Balrog: Archery kills Nazgul, and Balrog kills archery...<br />
Nelya (twilight): w/ Nazgul sword is absolutely deadly<br />
Black Steed: Good for overwhelms.  (Witch King w/ Pale Blade & Steed = 21 Str, Fierce and Damage + 1... ouch)<br />
Blade Tip over Black Breath: Blade Tip plays for free, and really hurts a small fellowship.<br />
All Blades Perish: Archery Protection... interchangeable w/ Relentless Charge, Fear, Their Power is in their Terror, or Nazgul Boosters.<br />
<br />
Thanks for your comments and reviews! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
